  "page": "Lord Costayne (Aerys I)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\"><img alt=\"House Costayne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/50px-House_Costayne.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/75px-House_Costayne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/100px-House_Costayne.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Lord Costayne</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\"><img alt=\"House Costayne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/50px-House_Costayne.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/75px-House_Costayne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/100px-House_Costayne.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Lord Costayne TMK comic.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png/300px-Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png/450px-Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png/600px-Lord_Costayne_TMK_comic.png 2x\" /></a><div>Lord Costayne, by Mike S. Miller</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Three_Towers\" title=\"Lord of the Three Towers\">Lord of the Three Towers</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\">House Costayne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Costayne_(Daeron_II)\" title=\"Lord Costayne (Daeron II)\">Costayne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nA daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lord Costayne</b> was the Lord of the <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Towers\" title=\"Three Towers\">Three Towers</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\">House Costayne</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>. He was married to one of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell</a>'s daughters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Costayne_(Aerys_I)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Costayne was younger than <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Shawney\" title=\"Lord Shawney\">Lord Shawney</a>, but considered himself better born.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Costayne_(Aerys_I)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a>, Lord Costayne's <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Costayne_(Daeron_II)\" title=\"Lord Costayne (Daeron II)\">lordly father</a> fought for <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon I Blackfyre</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">Battle of the Redgrass Field</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a>, Lord Costayne came with his retinue to <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls\" title=\"Whitewalls\">Whitewalls</a> to attend the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wedding\">wedding</a> of his father-in-law, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell</a>, and his second wife, <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Butterwell\" title=\"Lady Butterwell\">the daughter</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Frey\" title=\"Lord Frey\">Lord Frey</a>. On his way, Lord Costayne had to cross the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a> via a ferry. He quarreled with <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Shawney\" title=\"Lord Shawney\">Lord Shawney</a> on the matter of which lord should cross first; Shawney argued that as the older of the two he should go first, whereas Costayne believed that as <a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\">his House</a> was nobler then <a href=\"/index.php/House_Shawney\" title=\"House Shawney\">Shawney's</a>, he had the precedence.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the wedding feast, Lord Costayne was seated on the dais. The next day, he competed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_tourney_at_Whitewalls\" title=\"Wedding tourney at Whitewalls\">wedding tourney</a>, but lost to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Glendon_Flowers\" title=\"Glendon Flowers\">Glendon Flowers</a>. He sent his <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a> to ransom the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sorrel_(horse)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sorrel (horse)\">sorrel</a> he lost but Glendon decided to keep the <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a>. The angry lord told Glendon he had no right to use <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Ball\" title=\"Quentyn Ball\">Fireball</a>'s coat of arms. When Glendon was falsely accused of stealing a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon egg</a>, Lord Costayne advocated for Glendon to die.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The fate of Lord Costayne following the arrival at Whitewalls of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a>, and the suppression of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a> is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Costayne_(Aerys_I)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It's death that one deserves, not <a href=\"/index.php/Laws_and_justice_of_the_Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Laws and justice of the Seven Kingdoms\">justice</a>!<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Lord Costayne regarding <a href=\"/index.php/Glendon_Flowers\" title=\"Glendon Flowers\">Glendon Flowers</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Costayne_(Aerys_I)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Costayne_(Daeron_II)\" title=\"Lord Costayne (Daeron II)\">Lord Costayne</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose<br />Butterwell</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"bord